706512f-b.text:
(1)
Rockaway Ave., east side, north of Blake Ave., showing the First Congregational Church of New Lots, which was dedicated on May 31, 1869. The first services were held in June 1866, and a Sunday School was organized on July 28, 1868. Two lots 50' xY 120' were donated by G.S. Thatford. The church is 30' Y 45' and was erected at a cost of~3,500.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
Tho same, another view.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

706513f-a.text:
RtOckaway Ave., west side, between Blake and Sutter Aves., showing frame homes of the original Brownsville settlement. All these frame homes have been demolished, with the exception of the one next to the 4-story buildings
which is No. 546.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
